org.apache.taverna.reference.impl

Class T2ReferenceImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.reference.impl.T2ReferenceImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, HibernateComponentClass, T2Reference

    public class T2ReferenceImpl
extends Object
implements T2Reference, Serializable, HibernateComponentClass
    An implementation of T2Reference specific to the ReferenceSetImpl. This is needed because ReferenceSetImpl uses a component based primary key driven from the namespace and local parts of T2Reference. This in turn means we can query hibernate directly with a T2Reference instance in the data access object. Because this is only used as a component (i.e. a value type) we don't need to define a hibernate mapping file for it.
